Pre-Game Insights: Morocco’s head coach Walid Regragui announced the starting XI for the game against Zambia in the Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON).

Regragui’s starting team includes Yassine Bounou, Achraf Hakimi, Yahia Attiat Allah, Nayeef Aguerd, Sofyan Amrabat, Yunis Abdelhamid, Ismail Saibari, Azzedine Ounahi, Hakim Ziyech, Sofyan Boufal, and Ayoub El Kaabi.
Morocco has already qualified for the Round of 16 but aims to finish first in Group F.
Regragui mentioned that the game will take place at 9 p.m. Moroccan time, avoiding the daytime heat which has been challenging in past games.
Regragui emphasized the team's focus on winning the match to secure the top spot in the group.
Several predicting websites anticipate a victory for Morocco, with Opta analyst giving Morocco a 60.7% chance of victory compared to 18.5% for Zambia.
